Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Trim the @carrot{1} (no need to peel), quarter lengthways. Chop into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Peel and coarsely grate the @beetroot{1}(peeled and coarsely grated) (wash your hands straight after to avoid staining). Zest then halve the @lemon{1}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the onion and carrot and cook until softened, ~{5%minutes}. Stir in the @mild curry powder{1} and the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the @basmati rice{150}.

Pour the @water{300}(for the rice) into the saucepan, stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil!). When hot, add the @flaked almonds{15} and toast until golden, turning frequently, ~{2-3%minutes}. Once toasted, remove from the heat and pop into a #small bowl{}. Add the beetroot to a #large bowl{} and squeeze in half the lemon juice, a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Add half the parsley and stir together.

> TIP: Watch almonds like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Ten mins before the rice is ready, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in the now empty frying pan on medium heat, when hot add the @baby spinach{125} and lentils. Fry for a couple of mins, stirring occasionally, then cover the pan with a lid or some #foil{} and leave until the spinach has wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Once cooked, remove from the heat.

Once the rice is cooked fluff it up with a #fork{} and add the spinach and lentils (or add the rice to the spinach and lentils depending on which of your pans is bigger) along with the lemon zest and remaining parsley. Stir them in. Taste and add @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed. Serve the veggie pilaf in #bowls{} with the beetroot slaw on top and finish with a dollop of @low fat natural yoghurt{75} and a scattering of almonds. Enjoy!